http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Modi-responsible-for-crimes-in-Delhi-says-AAP-leader/article13994901.ece

The Narendra Modi government is responsible for every crime that takes place in the national Capital as Delhi Police comes under the Centre, AAP leader Alka Lamba said on Sunday as she asserted that the crime rate will drop if the AAP dispensation gets control of the force.Citing statistics by the National Crime Records Bureau, Ms Lamba, while addressing a rally here, said Madhya Pradesh tops the list of States in crime against women and that Chief Minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan was responsible for this.She also blamed Chouhan government for the deaths of people linked to Vyapam scam.Stating that the motto of the AAP government was to change the system, Ms Lamba said Mr Chouhan should emulate some of the good schemes implemented by the Delhi government.“Chouhan government should learn from the Arvind Kejriwal government about schemes like Mohalla Clinic as well as the education—related ones and try to implement them in Madhya Pradesh,” she said.Referring to a media report that Chouhan government was planning to implement carpooling formula for its ministers and other officials, she said, “Its good... it reflects that Kejriwal government’s schemes has its effect in Madhya Pradesh as well.” The AAP leader said that since the people of Madhya Pradesh are fed up with the BJP and the Congress, they will give a chance to AAP in the 2018 Assembly elections. -- PTI